<section>
  <slide>
    <title>Another column of slides</title>
    <theorem>
      <title>Cats and Mats</title>
      <statement><p>The cat sits on the mat.</p></statement>
      <proof><p>
        <ul slide-step="true">
          <li><p>Take cat and place near mat.</p></li>
          <li><p>Wait until cat is sat.</p></li>
          <li><p>Attempt to lift mat without disturbing cat.</p></li>
        </ul>
      </p></proof>
    </theorem>
  </slide>


  <slide>
    <title>Now without proof</title>
    <corollary>
      <title>Cats and bats</title>
      <statement><p>The cat eats the bat on the mat.</p></statement>
    </corollary>
    <p>
      <ul slide-step="true">
        <li><p>The proof is too long to fit in the margin here.</p></li>
        <li><p>It is left as an exercise for the reader.</p></li>
